    "headline": "United Rentals (NYSE:URI) Reports Upbeat Q2 CY2026, Stock Jumps 10.7%",
    "summary": "Equipment rental company United Rentals (NYSE:URI) reported Q2 CY2026 results beating Wall Street’s revenue expectations, with sales up 11.8% year on year to $4.41 billion. The company’s full-year revenue guidance of $17.65 billion at the midpoint came in 2.2% above analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $12.76 per share was 10.1% above analysts’ consensus estimates.",
